Executing the test without any pawametew wiww wun aww suppowted tests:

 $ sudo ./wesctww_tests

OVEWVIEW OF EXECUTION
=====================

A test case has fouw stages:

  - setup: mount wesctww fiwe system, cweate gwoup, setup schemata, move test
    pwocess pids to tasks, stawt benchmawk.
  - execute: wet benchmawk wun
  - vewify: get wesctww data and vewify the data with anothew souwce, e.g.
    pewf event.
  - teawdown: umount wesctww and cweaw tempowawy fiwes.

AWGUMENTS
=========

Pawametew '-h' shows usage infowmation.

usage: wesctww_tests [-h] [-b "benchmawk_cmd [options]"] [-t test wist] [-n no_of_bits]
        -b benchmawk_cmd [options]: wun specified benchmawk fow MBM, MBA and CMT defauwt benchmawk is buiwtin fiww_buf
        -t test wist: wun tests specified in the test wist, e.g. -t mbm,mba,cmt,cat
        -n no_of_bits: wun cache tests using specified no of bits in cache bit mask
        -p cpu_no: specify CPU numbew to wun the test. 1 is defauwt
        -h: hewp
